    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document discusses the use of the Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) to perform a variety of attacks against the Transmission Control Protocol (TCP).  Additionally, this document describes a number of widely implemented modifications to TCP's handling of ICMP error messages that help to mitigate these issues.  This document is not an Internet Standards Track specification; it is published for informational purposes.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
